== Kumato Salsa ==

Meanwhile, roughly chop @Kumato{2}(chopped), @Cucumber{1}(chopped) and @Parsley{1%packet}(chopped).

Finely chop @Garlic{2}(finely chopped).

Slice @Lemon{1} into wedges, set aside.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine Kumato, cucumber, parsley, @olive oil{1%drizzle} and a good squeeze of lemon juice. Season to taste.

== Garlic Yoghurt ==

In a #large frying pan{}, heat a drizzle of olive oil and garlic over medium-high heat, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Transfer to a #small bowl{}.

Add @Greek-Style Yoghurt{1%packet} to garlic oil mixture and combine. Season to taste.

== Paprika Chickpeas and Beef ==

Return #frying pan{} to medium-high heat.

Cook @Beef Mince{250%g} (no need for oil!), @chickpeas{1%packet}(half drained and rinsed) breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add @Tomato Paste{1%packet} and @Paprika Spice Blend{1%sachet} and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @reserved pasta water{1/3%cup} until combined, ~{1%minute}. Season to taste.

== Pasta ==

Half-fill a #large saucepan{} with water, add a generous pinch of @salt{}, then bring to the boil over high heat.

Cook @Orecchiette{1%packet} in boiling water until 'al dente', ~{11%minutes}.

Reserve pasta water. Drain orecchiette, then return to #saucepan{} with a drizzle of olive oil.

== To Serve ==

Divide orecchiette between bowls.

Top with garlic yoghurt then spoon over paprika chickpeas and beef.

Sprinkle over Kumato salsa and crumble over @Marinated Goat Cheese{1%packet}.

Drizzle over some goat cheese oil and serve with any remaining lemon wedges.

> Just before consuming, toss the pasta until combined, enjoy!